ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I think everybody should understand biochemistry to some level. This is what biology is today. It is no longer just a descriptive science. Non-scientists can't fully appreciate this distinction without some knowledge of biochemistry.
This course explains key biochemistry concepts and provides relevant examples of how this knowledge can help advance the field of medicine. Yes, I would recommend this course.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: My thesis project involves a fair amount of biochemistry. This course was a welcomed refresher.

This course provided me with a better understanding of biochemistry. I had not taken a biochem class before, but I need to have a fundamental understanding of this field for my research. Many of the topics in this course were directly relevant to my research.I audited this course and did not have interactions with any of the teaching fellows for the below questions.
